	<h1>About The Project</h1>
	</br>
	<div class="well well-lg">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-3">
				</br>
				<%= image_tag "pinterest.jpeg", height: '200', width: '250' %>
			</div>
			<div class='col-md-9'>
				<p><h4>The purpose of the project was to make a photo sharing app inspired by pinterest. So a user is able to sign in and post photos, as well as edit photos that they post. Anyone is able to see the posted photos, but you must be signed-in in order to add new photos. So there is a has-many relationship between photos and users, where a user has-many photos.</h4></p>
				<p><h4>*note* There is a known bug that exists with the display of the photos sometimes, at least on firefox (this bug doesn't seem to appear in safari). When you move to the homepage from somewhere else (like the about page) the photos overlap and don't look right. I'm still trying to figure out the cause of it, but I'm pretty sure it's caused by turbolinks that was added in rails 4. If you refresh the page the photos will appear normally again. </h4></p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
